The Minister of Power, Engr. Saleh Mamman has assured that the President Muhammadu Buhari government will deliver uninterrupted power to Nigeria before the expiration of the tenure in 2023. The Minister who gave the assurance in a statement in Kaduna, while inspecting power projects in the state, charged the distribution companies to utilise the power to be generated from the Kudenda Station. “I have assured Nigerians that President Muhammadu Buhari’s next level administration will deliver uninterrupted power supply to Nigeria before the end of its tenure,” he said. “I and the Minister of state for Power, Mr. Goddy Jeddy Agba are in Kaduna on a two-day working visit. “I have inspected the 330KV transmission station in Mando and Kaduna power plant in Kudenda. I have also assured the ministry ensure that ongoing power projects in the country are completed and power is delivered to the good people of Nigeria. ” have also charged the distribution companies to utilise the power to be generated from the Kudenda Station which is almost 86 percent completed.”